<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="511" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1189,1828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,348,1189,1215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Diagnosis. Male.</emphasis>
Postcranium black with gray pruinescence; thorax and abdomen shiny black, legs predominantly yellow (
<figureCitation box="[244,336,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); distal section of vein M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[620,628,1244,1258]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">4</subScript>
longer than vein dm-m (
<figureCitation box="[905,992,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); male tergite 8 acute distally (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1423,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); epandrium with posterodorsal lobe somewhat thin and higher than anterodorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1199,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); anterior cercus narrow, with distinct falciform mesial process (
<figureCitation box="[640,723,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
); cercal bridge small, subtriangular (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1205,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
); median cercus well elevated with distinct setae (
<figureCitation box="[459,544,1333,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); posterior cercus with three branches distally (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1174,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Figs 4E, F</figureCitation>
); ventral process of cercus inconspicuous; hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[511,596,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
) with few posterior setae at basal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1189,1828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1405,1431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Female</emphasis>
(
