<figureCitation box="[791,873,1441,1467]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4J</figureCitation>
